This article is a notice from the White House Office of the Press Secretary. It states that the national emergency declared on September 14, 2001, with respect to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001, will continue for another year. This is because the terrorist threat is still ongoing and there is a continued and immediate threat of further attacks on the United States. The powers and authorities adopted to deal with this emergency will also continue in effect beyond September 14, 2016. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress. The notice is signed by Barack Obama, the President at the time, and is dated August 30, 2016.